## Chapter03: Process Based Parallelism in Python

## 1 communicating_with_pipe.py
What I learned
In this program, 2 processes share data using a pipe. One process generates numbers, and the other receives them and calculates their square.

How to run
python communicating_with_pipe.py

Use
IPC (inter-process communication)

When use
When two processes need direct data exchange

Summary
Pipe-based process communication

Advantages
Fast communication
Simple method

Disadvantages
Best mainly for 2 processes

## 2 communicating_with_queue.py
What I learned

Producer-consumer model is used. Processes share data safely using a queue.

How to run
python communicating_with_queue.py

Use
Safe data sharing between processes

When use
When multiple processes need to share data

Summary
Queue communication system

Advantages
Safe & reliable
Easy to use

Disadvantages
Slower than pipe

## 3 killing_processes.py
What I learned
Shows how to forcefully stop a process using terminate().
How to run
python killing_processes.py
Use
Stopping unwanted processes
When use
When process hangs or takes too long
Summary
Process termination concept
Advantages
Easy process control
Disadvantages
May cause data loss

## 4 myFunc.py
What I learned
Simple reusable function that prints output based on process ID.
How to run
Imported in other files (not run directly)
Use
Helper function for multiprocessing
When use
When reusable logic is needed
Summary
Helper function file
Advantages
Reusable
Simple
Disadvantages
Limited functionality

## 5 naming_processes.py
What I learned
Processes are given custom names for identification.
How to run
python naming_processes.py
Use
Debugging and tracking processes
When use
When multiple processes need identification
Summary
Process naming system
Advantages
Easy debugging
Disadvantages
No synchronization feature

## 6 process_in_subclass.py
What I learned
Processes are created using class inheritance from multiprocessing.Process.
How to run
python process_in_subclass.py
Use
OOP-style multiprocessing
When use
When structured code is needed
Summary
Class-based process creation
Advantages
Clean structure
Reusable design
Disadvantages
Slightly complex

## 7 process_pool.py
What I learned
Uses a process pool to run multiple tasks in parallel.
How to run
python process_pool.py
Use
Parallel execution of multiple tasks
When use
When same task runs on many inputs
Summary
Process pool system
Advantages
Fast execution
Efficient
Disadvantages
Hard to manage sometimes

## 8 processes_barrier.py
What I learned
Processes are synchronized using a barrier and wait for each other.
How to run
python processes_barrier.py
Use
Process synchronization
When use
When coordination is required
Summary
Barrier synchronization
Advantages
Proper coordination
Disadvantages
Fixed number of processes required

## 9 run_background_processes_no_daemons.py
What I learned
Non-daemon processes run independently in the background.

How to run

python run_background_processes_no_daemons.py

Use
Long-running background tasks

When use
When independent execution is needed

Summary
Independent background processes

Advantages
Runs separately

Disadvantages
May continue after main program ends

## 10 run_background_processes.py
What I learned
Daemon processes stop automatically when the main program ends.

How to run
python run_background_processes.py

Use
Light background tasks

When use
When auto-stop behavior is needed

Summary
Daemon process concept
Advantages
Auto terminates

Disadvantages
Not independent

## 11 spawning_processes_namespace.py
What I learned
A process is created using functions imported from another file (modular approach).

How to run
python spawning_processes_namespace.py

Use
Modular multiprocessing

When use
Large structured projects

Summary
Modular process spawning

Advantages
Organized code

Disadvantages
Needs multiple files

## 12 spawning_processes.py
What I learned
Basic process creation using multiprocessing.Process.

How to run
python spawning_processes.py

Use
Running tasks in parallel processes

When use
Simple multiprocessing needed

Summary
Basic process spawning

Advantages
Easy to implement
Fast setup

Disadvantages
High memory usage